A Federal High Court sitting in Abuja adjourned a suit filed by Pinnacle Communications Limited (PCL) against the Independent Corrupt Practices and Other Related Offences Commission (ICPC) until November 6 for hearing.Pinnacle Communications in the suit No. FHC/ABJ/CS/779/18 has asked the court to order ICPC to pay it N1 billion for unlawfully withholding its money domiciled in Zenith Bank without a valid court order.The matter was originally slated for hearing on Tuesday, but it could not hold due to the absence of Justice Taiwo Taiwo, who was away on another official assignment.